  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with metastatic breast cancer considered HER2 negative are screened for
      HER2-amplified circulating tumor cells. If at least HER2-amplified circulating tumor cell is
      detected, patients are treated by Trastuzumab - Emtansine (T-DM1) in a single arm phase II
      with an adaptive design.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
